  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other crimes) appear to come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal money into the financial system\n2. Layering - concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - making the money seem legally earned\n\nIt's illegal in most countries and can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n- Hefty fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nIf you're dealing with financial concerns, it's always best to consult a legal professional or financial advisor.",
